simulation.simulation

Class Simulation

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulation.simulation.Simulation

  • public class Simulation
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing the process of simulation of computer model of language competition.

      • Simulation

        public Simulation(Environment environment,
                  java.util.Collection<Language> languages,
                  Population population,
                  InteractionRunner interactionRunner,
                  VariantAgent variantAgent,
                  int variantInfluence)
        Initializes this simulation with the given arguments.
        Parameters:
        environment - the initial environment for this simulation
        languages - the collection of languages competing in this simulation
        population - the population of agents interacting in this simulation
        interactionRunner - the interaction runner for interactions in this simulation
        variantAgent - a variant agent for this simulation
        variantInfluence - number of interactions of the given variant agents in each simulation's step

    • Method Detail

      • simulateOneStep

        public void simulateOneStep()
        Simulates a number of interactions within the population of agents equal to the size of this population. If a variant agent is specified, it simulates variantInfluence interactions with the variant agent before the interactions between agents.

      • agentsLexicallySynchronized

        public boolean agentsLexicallySynchronized()
